parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power sliding doors can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when the doors open or close unexpectedly while the vehicle is in motion.
symptoms: The power sliding doors may not open or close properly
jam
stick
or open unexpectedly while driving
causing a distraction to the driver. The doors may also fail to latch or unlock
making it difficult to enter or exit the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hood latch can cause the hood to fly open while driving, obstructing the driver's view and potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The hood may fly open while driving
causing damage to the hood and windshield. The hood latch may also fail to engage
making it difficult to close the hood.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear sliding doors can cause inconvenience, safety risks, and potential accidents, especially when the doors open or close unexpectedly while driving.
symptoms: The rear sliding doors operate independently
open or close unexpectedly
do not open or close properly
the door handle falls off
and the doors do not respond to the ceiling button.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause unexpected behavior of various vehicle systems, leading to safety risks, inconvenience, and potential accidents.
symptoms: The engine warning light illuminates
the charging system pulses the headlamps
the interior and exterior lighting fails
the ESC indicator light becomes illuminated
and the rear lights remain illuminated with the engine turned off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the starter motor can cause the vehicle to fail to start, leading to inconvenience and potential safety risks.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to start
and the starter motor needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the radio/CD/tape deck can cause inconvenience and distraction while driving.
symptoms: The radio/CD/tape deck does not properly load tapes/CDs
and the system may experience electrical shorts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front lower control arm can cause the vehicle to lose steering control, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. This failure can also cause the tire to detach from the vehicle, resulting in a loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle makes a clunking or squealing noise while driving
the steering wheel turns sideways while the wheels remain straight
the ESC off warning light illuminates on the instrument panel
the front control arm fractures or corrodes
and the vehicle loses steering ability.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Corrosion of Front Lower Control Arm
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the front lower control arm can cause the vehicle to lose steering control, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. This corrosion can also cause the tire to detach from the vehicle, resulting in a loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle makes a loud thumping noise
the front control arm corrodes or disintegrates
the axle comes out of the transmission
and the vehicle loses steering ability.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inadequate repair of the front lower control arm during the recall can cause the vehicle to lose steering control, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle still experiences corrosion and rust on the front lower control arm despite the recall repair
and the vehicle makes a horrible metal-to-metal grinding noise in the front end.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS module can cause an electrical short circuit, leading to an engine compartment fire, even when the vehicle is turned off, increasing the risk of injury.
symptoms: Thick white smoke coming from underneath the engine hood
flames seen coming from under the vehicle
smoke and fire despite the engine being off
and warning lights on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to complete the recall repair can leave the vehicle vulnerable to the original safety risk, which in this case is the ABS module failure.
symptoms: Dealer unable to provide recall repair due to incorrect parts
part being on backorder
and inability to complete the repair despite multiple attempts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal can cause the pedal to travel all the way down to the floorboard, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal travels all the way down to the floorboard
and no warning indicators illuminated.
